## Authentication

### Two-Legged OAuth (Client Credentials)

For server-to-server integrations using client credentials:

```ruby
require '{{langConfig.gemName}}'

client = {{moduleName}}::Client.new(
  domain: "your-institution.blackboard.com",
  client_id: "your-client-id",
  client_secret: "your-client-secret"
)
```

### Three-Legged OAuth (Authorization Code + PKCE)

For user-delegated access (e.g., acting on behalf of a student or instructor):

```ruby
require '{{langConfig.gemName}}'

auth = {{moduleName}}::OAuth2Client.new(
  base_url: "https://your-institution.blackboard.com",
  client_id: "your-client-id",
  client_secret: "your-client-secret",
  token_endpoint: "{{auth.twoLegged.tokenEndpoint}}"
)

# Step 1: Generate the authorization URL with PKCE
result = auth.get_authorization_url(
  redirect_uri: "https://your-app.com/callback",
  scope: "read",
  state: "csrf-tok"
)
# Redirect the user to result.url
# Store result.code_verifier

# Step 2: After the user authorizes, exchange the code
auth.exchange_code(
  code: code_from_callback,
  redirect_uri: "https://your-app.com/callback",
  code_verifier: result.code_verifier
)

# The auth client now holds the user's access token
token = auth.get_token
```

## Quick Start

```ruby
# List courses
courses = client.courses.list
puts courses

# Get a single course
course = client.courses.get("externalId:INTRO-101")
puts course["name"]
```

## Error Handling

```ruby
require '{{langConfig.gemName}}'

begin
  course = client.courses.get("_invalid_id_")
rescue {{moduleName}}::NotFoundError
  puts "Course not found"
rescue {{moduleName}}::RateLimitError => e
  puts "Rate limited — retry after #{e.retry_after}s"
rescue {{moduleName}}::APIError => e
  puts "API error #{e.status}: #{e.message}"
end
```

## Pagination

Paginated methods return lazy enumerators:

```ruby
client.courses.list_all.each do |course|
  puts course["name"]
end
```

